  "solution": {
    "approach": "Observe that x⊕(x+1) equals (x+2)⊕(x+3) iff the lowest set bit of x is at position 0, i.e., x is even. In the range [0, 2^N‑1] exactly half of the numbers are even, giving 2^{N-1} valid x. Hence the answer is 2^{N-1} modulo 1e9+7. Compute this power with binary exponentiation for each test case.",
    "timeComplexity": "O(T·log N) – binary exponentiation per test case (log N ≤ 17 for N ≤ 100000).",
    "spaceComplexity": "O(1) additional space.",
    "code": {
      "C": "",
      "C++": "",
      "Java": "import java.io.*;\nimport java.util.*;\n\npublic class Main {\n    private static final long MOD = 1_000_000_007L;\n    private static long modPow(long exp) {\n        long result = 1L;\n        long base = 2L;\n        while (exp > 0) {\n            if ((exp & 1L) == 1L) {\n                result = (result * base) % MOD;\n            }\n            base = (base * base) % MOD;\n            exp >>= 1L;\n        }\n        return result;\n    }\n    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n        BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(System.in));\n        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\n        int T = Integer.parseInt(br.readLine().trim());\n        for (int i = 0; i < T; i++) {\n            long N = Long.parseLong(br.readLine().trim());\n            sb.append(modPow(N - 1)).append('\\n');\n        }\n        System.out.print(sb.toString());\n    }\n}",
      "Python3": "",
      "JavaScript": ""
    }
  },
